<task id="001" project="sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix">
  <metadata>
    <title>Owner sign-off on design.md §3 Resolved Decisions</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort>~15 min (single-owner ACK via task-execute)</actual-effort>
    <assigned>Project owner</assigned>
    <started>2026-05-24</started>
    <completed>2026-05-24</completed>
    <tags>coordination, governance, phase-0</tags>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>First task; sequential gate for all other Phase 0 work</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Obtain explicit owner sign-off on each of the 9 Resolved Decisions in design.md §3.
    This is the project's authorization gate — no other Phase 0 work proceeds until each
    decision is confirmed (or explicitly overridden) by the project owner. Sign-off is recorded
    as a PR comment on the project branch or as an entry in this task's completion notes.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Project coordinator. Not a code change — this is a stakeholder approval task.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Each of the 9 Resolved Decisions in design.md §3 has an explicit owner ACK or override,
    recorded in this task's completion notes. The Phase 0 checklist in design.md §6 Phase 0
    has items 1–2 checked.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="ai-spec">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/CLAUDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="design.md">No Phase 1+ work proceeds without this sign-off</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Override of a Resolved Decision must include a written rationale in the task notes</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/design.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/spec.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      design.md §3 captures 9 Resolved Decisions arising from approach.md §9 open questions plus
      late-2026-05-20 additions (test path, vulnerability remediation scope, sole-approver risk,
      extraction-assessment resolution). The owner authored design.md but the project convention is
      that an explicit sign-off step makes the assumptions binding.
    </background>
    <dependencies>None — this is the first project task</dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read design.md §3 Resolved Decisions table (9 rows)</step>
    <step order="2">For each decision, the owner ACKs as-is OR provides an override with written rationale</step>
    <step order="3">Record outcomes in this task's completion notes (or as a PR comment on the project branch)</step>
    <step order="4">Update design.md §6 Phase 0 checklist items 1–2 to checked</step>
    <step order="5">Update TASK-INDEX.md status of task 001 from 🔲 to ✅</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="git">For PR comment / status update if used as the signed-off record</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/tasks/001-*.poml (status: complete)</output>
    <output type="docs">design.md §6 Phase 0 checklist items 1–2 checked (if owner edits design.md) OR PR comment</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (status update for 001)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All 9 §3 Resolved Decisions have owner ACK or override</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">design.md §6 Phase 0 checklist items 1–2 marked complete OR equivalent PR comment exists</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">TASK-INDEX.md shows 001 as ✅</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    <completion-summary>
      Owner ACK'd all 9 §3 Resolved Decisions as-is on 2026-05-24 via task-execute Skill invocation.
      Sign-off recorded in design.md §6 Phase 0 checklist (items 1–2 checked, item 6 marked N/A per
      operator-only override, item 7 already pre-resolved 2026-05-20).
    </completion-summary>

    <decisions-acked>
      <decision n="1">Prod deploy process scope — Define before Phase 5; if no canonical process at Phase 0 close, scope = dev+demo only (deferred to task 003)</decision>
      <decision n="2">App Insights baseline window — 48 hours</decision>
      <decision n="3">CI guard size regression tolerance — Hard fail by default + [allow-size-growth] PR-label escape (codified in task 070)</decision>
      <decision n="4">Quarterly review cadence ownership — Project owner (codified in task 079 SKILL.md next-review-date)</decision>
      <decision n="5">Scope of "BFF" — Sprk.Bff.Api.csproj first; Spaarke.Core/Spaarke.Dataverse inventory only</decision>
      <decision n="6">Test project location — tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ (factual correction; verified at pre-flight)</decision>
      <decision n="7">dotnet build --warnaserror — DO NOT use; Phase 3 baselines warning count, Phase 4 verifies no new warnings (task 031)</decision>
      <decision n="8">Vulnerability remediation scope — In scope as Outcome B (parallel to size); per-package risk profile</decision>
      <decision n="9">Sole-approver risk — OVERRIDDEN 2026-05-24 via operator-only model (NFR-08 revised, UQ-01 RESOLVED). Replaces "dual approval required" with owner + AI-directed adr-check/code-review + CI gates (FR-C1–C6). Task 002 documents the model.</decision>
    </decisions-acked>

    <next-task>002 (parallel-safe Group A) — task 001 unblocks tasks 002, 003, 004, 005, 006, 007, 009. Operator can dispatch these in parallel per TASK-INDEX.md Parallel Execution Groups (Group A coordination), with task 009 sequential by its parallel-reason. Task 008 (Phase 0 gate) waits on all of them.</next-task>
  </notes>
</task>
